Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.43,0:02:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I tell you, what the hell is\Nthat fool doing anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.16,0:02:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought him a t-shirt that I thought\Nwould look good on him and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come, come. they'll be home soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.36,0:02:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this key holder?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.83,0:02:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, a kindly looking\Nold man gave it us on the bus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.97,0:02:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh the man who gave us\Nhis seat saying that we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.34,0:03:00.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iooked to be carrying a heavy load...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.71,0:03:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you so very much
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.94,0:03:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.51,0:03:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U.Uh. where are you girls living?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.71,0:03:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to pick us up. mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.48,0:03:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.82,0:03:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,NN. No. I run an antique shop at Haidocho...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.56,0:03:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I thought I'd like you to drop in one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.56,0:03:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haidocho is nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.69,0:03:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My house is right next\Nto it on Beikacho 5-chome
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.56,0:03:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O.Oh. . 5 chome...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.23,0:03:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we go tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.20,0:03:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay. let's!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.63,0:03:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll give you the catalog\Nof my shop and a key holder...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.57,0:03:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P.Promise. okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.11,0:03:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what a key holder
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:37.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that brings flourishing(business is all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.18,0:03:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go, Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.05,0:03:45.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The four red horses...\Nthat were found at the serial arson sites!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.87,0:03:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went way out to ask\Nthe forensic officers for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.66,0:03:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you'd better find some sort of a clue,\Nor you're going to get it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not the one who\Nwant to see the horses, they do...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.00,0:03:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come...only this horse\Nfrom the first fire 1s burnt black like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.23,0:04:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And only this horse has a stand...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.84,0:04:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? There's something written\Non the back of the stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.31,0:04:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.44,0:04:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey... A red horse and rabbit...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.11,0:04:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D:Donrt tell me that.+
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. isn't this... Kanu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.25,0:04:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kanuyis the military commander who\Nappears in the story Sangokusht, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.35,0:04:19.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.39,0:04:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kanu is/also famous for being the god\Nof prosperity for doing business
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.76,0:04:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. what a flashy colored\Nhorse he's riding
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.06,0:04:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a "Sekitouba (Red Rabbit Horse)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a super horse said to be able\Nto run a thousand miles in a day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.40,0:04:35.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Red Rabbit Horse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.14,0:04:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that this red plastic horse is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.21,0:04:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a famous horse that\Nappears in Sagokushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.01,0:04:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.38,0:04:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try looking at the stand of this horse\Nthat was left at the first scene of the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You-can't read the words above\Nand under it because they re burnt,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.88,0:04:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you can see the word rabbit. right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.15,0:04:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, true...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.06,0:04:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only red horse with the word rabbit\Nto its name is the horse
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.16,0:05:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that ran around battlefields\NWI 1S VICIOUS MI I ary comman er
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.66,0:05:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on its back, Red Rabbit Horse, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did the arsonist put the legendary\Nhorse that appears in an old Chinese story
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.93,0:05:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at the sites he set fire to?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.20,0:05:10.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.07,0:05:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,China...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.17,0:05:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,China...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.44,0:05:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Feng Shui is also from China. isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.28,0:05:20.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who came to the\NMorozumi residence before the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,didn't he say anything\Nto Ryoko about the old Chinese story?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.15,0:05:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't say anything about Sangokushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.69,0:05:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but that Sensei of Feng Shui's got\Na perfect motive
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.66,0:05:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.69,0:05:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was looking for\Nthe video tape of his affair
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.30,0:05:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with Ryoko Morozumi\Nwho died in the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.57,0:05:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't™be!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.17,0:05:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get rid of the video tape\Nhe burned down the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.24,0:05:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yuminaga!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.14,0:05:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.21,0:05:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! If you find out anything more,\Nplease report to me again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.15,0:05:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes sir
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.08,0:06:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the ones\Nwith motive is not limited to that Sensei
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.42,0:06:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keiko Gondo. the fortuneteller that came\Nto the house before the Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.43,0:06:08.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems that she's\Ngoing to get a large sum
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.68,0:06:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of estate from her parents being\Nthat she's oko's older-sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:17.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it that fortuneteller-was\Nsaying that their father just died!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.34,0:06:20.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that lady came to borrow\Nmoney from Ryoko
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.58,0:06:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she was going to inherit the estate\Nof her father anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.18,0:06:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,why would she do something like that...
