Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.75,0:06:30.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His only living relatives were\Nhis two daughters Ryoko and Keiko
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.05,0:06:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seems to have left\Na will saying that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.06,0:06:39.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would leave his entire estate to Ryoko\Nwho had taken a husband
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.06,0:06:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I 888...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.40,0:06:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so if Ryoko disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.43,0:06:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the estate that she originally couldn't\Ninherit would be hers...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.70,0:06:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.64,0:06:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because there was nothing\Non the death note that said,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.89,0:06:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if the younger sister dies,\Ndon-t7give it to the older sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.54,0:06:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.48,0:06:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryoko's husband is clean!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.68,0:07:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If his wife dies he loses\Nthe estate and all...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...not really so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.05,0:07:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her husband Akira\NMorozumi is a psychiatrist,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.66,0:07:08.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and wanted to demolish that house
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.96,0:07:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that they were living in\Nand build his own hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.56,0:07:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since Ryoko was opposed to it,\Nhe seems to have been in a fix...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.78,0:07:19.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seems to have been given\Nthat land and house by Ryoko's parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.10,0:07:25.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On top of that, if he knew that his wife\Nwas having an extra-maritalzaffair,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.01,0:07:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would have more\Nthan enough motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.11,0:07:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is all three\Nof them have an alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.05,0:07:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.85,0:07:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the time the arsonist setfire and put\Nthis horse at the site was around 7:30 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.52,0:07:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her husband came home\Nabout 10 minutes before that but,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.92,0:07:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after that before\Neven a minute had passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.53,0:07:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he went out drinking\Nwith the Sensei of Feng Shu
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.00,0:07:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.60,0:07:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the fortuneteller was telling fortunes\Nin a building in front of Haido:Station... =~.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.17,0:07:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the only suspect left is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:08:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the-man who was at the front door of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.51,0:08:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the Morozumi residence\Nwhen we got there...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.05,0:08:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who tried to leave\Nthe catalog of the things in his store and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.82,0:08:10.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,key holder that would help business prosper.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.18,0:08:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But was asked to leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.72,0:08:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner of the antique store,\Nat timid looking man...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless we can figure out\Nwho and where he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.83,0:08:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.70,0:08:27.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, this horse that was\Nfound at the first fire site?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.70,0:08:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only this horse has a strange protrusion\Non its body!
