Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.67,0:09:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They get me so mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:38.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's just forget about those\Nguys and go to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.81,0:09:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.34,0:09:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't we hang this\Nsunny boy doll out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.04,0:09:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the veranda of dad's room so\Nthat it doesn't rain tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.51,0:09:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it didn't seem to work last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.82,0:09:53.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to wish with all my\Nmight tonight so that it works!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.89,0:09:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.92,0:10:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've found them. I've finally found them...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.73,0:10:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.60,0:10:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He once came up as a suspect?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.37,0:10:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are:you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.90,0:10:10.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. his name is TakanorilGérita
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.97,0:10:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's running an antique shop in\NHaidecho just as you assumed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.78,0:10:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. why'd, ou suspect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.21,0:10:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was among the crowd of*onlookers\Nat the fire site at Rizencho
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.82,0:10:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was mumbling something\Nstrange while watching the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.14,0:10:30.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was saying...Father ..Father
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.52,0:10:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.73,0:10:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His father used to be a firefighter. and\Nwhen he was still in elementary school,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.06,0:10:39.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,his father tried to save a person who\Ncouldn't make it out of the fire'in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.43,0:10:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was swallowed by the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.14,0:10:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D.Don't tell me thatthe man 1s .
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.11,0:10:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we, the police thought so too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.61,0:10:51.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he set fire in memory of his father
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.95,0:10:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That . maybe he thought that if he caused
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.57,0:10:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a fire his father would\Ncome dashing to the scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.86,0:11:05.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so not being able\Nto give up hope, he started
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.56,0:11:07.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,setting fires from 1-chome in sequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.06,0:11:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Kept chasing the illusion\Nof his father
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.15,0:11:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 5.00 in the evening, he stopped by\Nat the shop once and then went home?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.27,0:11:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. he said he was tired
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been distributing\Ncatalogs of our store and key
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.18,0:11:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,holders to people in the\Nneighborhood from morning so
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that key holder the one with\Na person riding a red horse
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.29,0:11:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. it's his work of effort\Nof the statue of Kanu
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.52,0:11:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, he changed it to another key.holder\Nbecause it didn t take too well to others
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? He changed it?
